{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"layoutPriority","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"_","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"value","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Double","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"value","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The priority by which a parent layout apportions","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"space to the child.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Views typically have a default priority of ","type":"text"},{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which causes space to be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"apportioned evenly to all sibling views. Raising a view’s layout","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"priority encourages the higher priority view to shrink later when the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"group is shrunk and stretch sooner when the group is stretched.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["HStack {","    Text(\"This is a moderately long string.\")","        .font(.largeTitle)","        .border(Color.gray)","","    Spacer()","","    Text(\"This is a higher priority string.\")","        .font(.largeTitle)","        .layoutPriority(1)","        .border(Color.gray)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the example above, the first "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" element has the default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"priority "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":" which causes its view to shrink dramatically due to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"higher priority of the second "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Text","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" element, even though all of their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"other attributes (font, font size and character count) are the same."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A parent layout offers the child views with the highest layout priority"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all the space offered to the parent minus the minimum space required for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all its lower-priority children."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"platforms":[{"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false}],"modules":[{"name":"OpenSwiftUI","relatedModules":["OpenSwiftUICore"]}],"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"layoutPriority(_:)","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE14layoutPriorityyQrSdF::SYNTHESIZED::s:15OpenSwift